RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Claiming Purse 21000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 118 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $20,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NINETYNINECARATS broke on top then settled into stride, stalked the dueling leaders into the turn, swept to the front four wide coming to the top of the stretch, was given just moderate urging in the late stages when willingly holding the inside rival at bay to be best. UPTOWN JIVE broke in just a bit lightly bumping a rival and soon went to the early lead, was challenged after the opening three-sixteenths, dueled outside a foe and put to urging about the five-sixteenths regaining the lead, was overtaken by an outside rival at the top of the stretch, fought on inside that one but was only second best. RITZ ON BROADWAY bumped with a rival at the start, raced in the trailing group between runners moving out from two to four wide on the turn, was guided out further in upper stretch and ran on to get show honors. TRICKY RIVER broke a step slowly after getting bumped just lightly at the start, was urged strongly to gain forward position drawing even at the half, dueled with a narrow advantage inside a rival to the five-sixteenths, was overtaken by the outside foe past that marker, gave way in the stretch. BOBBI TWO STEPS lacked early speed despite some urging, raced outside at the back four to five wide through the turn, was never near enough to threaten. PRINCESS PEANUT bumped with a foe at the start, raced at the back inside, was not a threat.

ENTRY.NAME: Tricky River
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, urged forward, led 1/2, duel, gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Uptown Jive
ENTRY.COMMENT: early lead, duel outside, ask 5/16 & led to 3/16, fought on insd

ENTRY.NAME: Princess Peanut
ENTRY.COMMENT: bump brk, inside, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Ritz On Broadway
ENTRY.COMMENT: bump brk, 2-4w turn, came out upper, ran on

ENTRY.NAME: Bobbi Two Steps
ENTRY.COMMENT: no speed, outside, 4-5w turn, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Ninetyninecarats
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked duel, swept to lead 4wide 3/16, best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 2 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 92. Starter Allowance Purse 20000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $6,250 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 26, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race At A Mile Or Over Since April 26, 2023 Allowed 4 lbs. (Maiden And Claiming Races For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIZ HERSELF moved forward setting the pace from off the rail in the two to three path, was pressed briefly early up the backstretch by an outside rival, edged clear of that one heading to the far turn, was challenged again by that same foe coming to the quarter pole, was on even terms with that one through upper- to mid-stretch while possibly just headed, dug in to inch away late. WHYISSHESOOLUCKY was caught five wide into the first turn, moved forward outside foes on that bend and shifted in a path, pressed the leader briefly up the backstretch, lost ground on that one, regained momentum on the far turn to bid coming to the quarter pole, was even through mid-stretch but fended off late. MAVILUS settled off the leaders into the first turn, saved ground tracking inside, came out a bit leaving the far turn just off the leading pair, moved out further in upper stretch, was no match for the top pair. CHALK HILL was taken back from outside runners into the first turn shifting in to the three to four path, moved back out leaving that bend and advanced a bit up the backstretch, was guided back nearer inside racing in the three path and ridden along three furlongs out, came out for the drive and ran on without threatening. REINA LA KELSY chased briefly three wide through the first turn, dropped back between runners up the backstretch, faded. MONIQUES DAREDEVIL was caught four then three wide on the first turn, raced off the pace still wide into the far turn, was never near enough to threaten.

ENTRY.NAME: Mavilus
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, tracked inside, came out upper, no match top pair

ENTRY.NAME: Tiz Herself
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace, off rail, 2-3path, challenged 1/4, dug in, inched away late

ENTRY.COMMENT: 4-5w, bid 1/4, fended off

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 74. Maiden Special Weight Purse 38000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 119 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NUTELLA FELLA was very fractious in the gate, exchanged some bumps at the start and was consequently away a length slowly, moved forward willingly between runners up the backstretch, tucked in behind the leaders racing in the two path into the turn, was guided out late on that bend and altered outside the leader coming to the top of the stretch, took the measure of that one and was in command at the furlong marker, drew clear. LINZER got away alertly, ceded the lead content to shadow while kept very wide to the far turn, moved in from the four to the three path early on that bend, took the lead about the five-sixteenths and came back out turning for home, was overtaken by mid-stretch and second best. FULMINEO pursued from outside entering the turn four deep, moved in a path on that bend racing in behind the leading trio, moved out again turning for home, was no match but best of the rest. INCHON bumped lightly with a rival at the start, was outsprinted early, moved out from two to four wide on the turn, ran on. FINICKY bobbled and bumped with a rival at the start, was urged to the lead, set the pace racing inside into the turn, gave way in the stretch. JIGGERY POKERY chased from between runners, shifted in a bit but still off the fence through the turn, failed to menace. BEYOND REPROACH broke a step slowly, was urged forward to chase inside, dropped back, came out in upper stretch, failed to rally.

ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, urged forward, dropped back, came out upper

ENTRY.NAME: Inchon
ENTRY.COMMENT: light bump brk, 2-4w turn, ran on

ENTRY.NAME: Nutella Fella
ENTRY.COMMENT: very fractious, bumps brk, forwardly btw, 2-4w turn, led 1/8, clr

ENTRY.NAME: Finicky

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 14000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS OR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since June 26, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ZIPPER ZAPPER set the early pace while kept off the rail in the two to three path, was pressured midway up the backstretch and overtaken by the half, dropped back into the far turn, switched out at the five-sixteenths and began to advance again, fanned seven wide into upper stretch as leading pair drifted out, struck the lead near the sixteenth pole and edged past. THE COLORA KID stalked off the early leaders four wide, took closer order willingly advancing outside up the backstretch, took the lead at the half in tandem with an inside foe, dispatch that one soon after and was clear on the far turn, drifted out a couple paths turning for home, continued out a bit further in upper stretch, was overtaken inside the final furlong, outfinished but second best. MR BOLDACIOUS lacked early speed, was taken in hand and angled in early, saved ground through the first turn racing well back, advanced on the leaders on the far turn passing outside a rival, was one-paced in the lane. HIS ROYAL G stalked the leader four then three wide in the early going, moved along with an outside rival to bid between coming to the half, tried to go on with the outside one but could not, drifted out a couple paths leaving the far turn and weakened. GABBYS BIG NOTION shifted in but off the fence heading into the first turn, raced at the back and failed to meance. IM YOUR PAPI tracked mid-division in the three then two path in the early going, dropped back and faded.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 69. Maiden Special Weight Purse 38000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD WEIGHT, 118 LBS. (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LAGONISI moved forward between runners into the first turn two wide, set the pace on a narrow advantage, was challenged in earnest by the inside runner at the half, dispatched that one early on the far turn, was challenged by an outside rival coming to the quarter while drifting out turning for home, turned back that rival and drew clear in upper stretch then was kept to the task. LOTUS CASE broke just a half-step slowly then moved forward under mild coaxing, caught three wide among and outside the leaders into the first turn, eased back off a pair content to stalk from outside, advanced on the far turn making a bid at the quarter pole and being floated five wide leaving that bend, could not match strides with the winner but was second best. AMORICA broke sharply, was soon overtaken into the first turn, pressed from inside, took closer order to force the issue at the half, was dispatched early on the far turn, weakened in continued pursuit. LADY CHA CHA raced two to three wide off the early pace, edged closer on the far turn in behind the leaders, flattened out in the drive. URSULINE settled mid-pack inside, came out a bit for the stretch run, was never near enough to threaten. CUNDI was loaded backwards into the gate, raced outside off the pace three wide early, was not a threat. MISS MELODRAMATIC raced at the rear off the inside and made no impact.

PIT STOP MAN eased back off the leaders, switched outside those stalking, went four wide on the turn, kept on to gain the place while no threat to the winner. REBEL EMPIRE broke on top and set the pace facing pressure from the eventual winner outside, raced off the rail through the turn, was overtaken by the top of the stretch, drifted in a bit in mid-stretch, weakened some but kept on well enough to hold show.
